'''Urufushine Shrine''' (うるふしねじんじゃ) is a shrine {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=enshrined|1=UNKNOWN}} in Hirao, {{ill|lt=Nabari|Q166183|WD=Q166183|1=Nabari, Mie}}, {{ill|lt=Mie Prefecture|Q128196|WD=Q128196|1=Mie Prefecture}}.

It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}, and its former rank was {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=kensha|1=Ken-sha|WD=Q90139226}}.

Today, the character for "fu" in Urufushine is commonly written as "冨".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Urufushine Shrine|url=http://urufushine.jp/|access-date=2025-9-2}}</ref>

About the origin of the main deity Unane-no-Mikoto, it is explained as deriving from "(Nabari) River meanders => unane."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Urufushine Shrine|url=http://urufushine.jp/intro.html#a03|access-date=2025-9-1}}</ref>

"Benten-iwa" on the Nabari River bank west of the shrine is the sacred body<ref>{{Cite web|title=Urufushine Shrine Rock Festival|website=Iwa net|url=https://iwashinbun.com/?special=%e5%ae%87%e6%b5%81%e5%86%a8%e5%bf%97%e7%a6%b0%e7%a5%9e%e7%a4%be-%e5%b2%a9%e7%a5%ad%e3%82%8a|access-date=2025-11-7}}</ref>.

=== History ===
In {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|WD=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 8 ({{ill|lt=1580|Q6712|WD=Q6712|1=1580}}), all shrine buildings, treasures, and old documents were lost in the {{ill|lt=Tenshō Iga Rebellion|Q15436846|WD=Q15436846|1=Tenshō Iga War}}.

Founding is unknown. The 'Kasuga Shaki' says that in {{ill|lt=Jingokeiun|Q1373049|WD=Q1373049|1=Jingo-keiun}} 1 ({{ill|lt=767|Q30561|WD=Q30561|1=AD 767}}), when Takemikazuchi-no-Kami moved from {{ill|lt=Kashima Jingū|Q706499|WD=Q706499|1=Kashima Jingū}} to {{ill|lt=Kasuga Taisha|Q714559|WD=Q714559|1=Kasuga-taisha}}, he remained here, and this is the origin.

In the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|WD=Q333530|1=Emperor Sujin}}, "Yamatohime Seiki / Jingū-go Chinzaki" says "second year {{ill|lt=hōsai|Q381353|WD=Q381353|1=Women writers}}" and records that {{ill|lt=Yamatohime-no-Mikoto|Q4388732|WD=Q4388732|lt=Yamatohime|1=Yamatohime-no-mikoto}} made a circuit to this shrine, indicating it was a {{ill|lt=Moto-Ise|Q11387775|WD=Q11387775|1=Moto-Ise Shrines}} site.

In '{{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q1052981|lt=Sandai Jitsuroku|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}', in {{ill|lt=Jōgan (Japan)|Q1075635|WD=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} 15 ({{ill|lt=873|Q30369|WD=Q30369|1=873}}), Unane deity is Senior Fifth Rank Upper. Later the rank rose gradually, reaching Junior First Rank in {{ill|lt=Eitoku|Q1145805|WD=Q1145805|1=Eitoku}} 1 ({{ill|lt=1387|Q6359|WD=Q6359|1=1387}}).

=== Enshrined deities ===
